latestPosts.caption:
Namaste.

Today, I wear a saree — a symbol of our tradition, grace, and strength.

Just like yoga —
It’s deeply Indian.
Rooted in the wisdom of our ancestors.

Yoga is not just movement.
It’s a journey — inward.

A path to grow — spiritually, physically, mentally, emotionally.

It helps us rise — beyond our limits,
beyond our fears,
beyond the noise.

It teaches us to be present.
To breathe.
To connect.

Yoga is not a trend.
It’s a legacy.

On this International Yoga Day,
let us honor this gift from our land —
with awareness, with action and with love.

Namaste.

- Abharana

🙏🏽🪷

Ever noticed how, no matter how much you wish for something,
it doesn’t always unfold the way you imagined?

The missed chances, the quiet goodbyes, the doors that didn’t open —
they weren’t punishments.
They were protection. Redirection. Divine timing.

She — life, the universe, 
the divine — is always working in your favor.
Even when it doesn’t look like it.

Trust her.
Let go.
And allow it all to unfold in its own sacred way🍃

Live , love , create new experiences, memories. 
Seriously live your life!

1) Take a step closer to love, 1% growth better than nothing, half step is greater than no step.
2) Sometimes don’t take yourself/ life seriously,
Remember we are in the middle of nowhere , out of trillions of galaxies.
3) Happiness is a habit. The more you learn to make youself happy, life gets beautiful.
4) coming back to your home( the self ) , can be done by simply moving your body wherever you are. keep trying , do everything, never give up. 
5) Living and thriving is easier than ever because we have easy access to the “tools”
6 ) Surrender, allow the divine to lead you, love you , show you the way.
7) Pray ; the divine is always listening to you, wants the best for you.
8) Be delusional, always. Don’t listen to the society / anyone. It’s a scam , that you have to listen and follow.
9) There’s no blueprint to life , carve your way out. But Don’t miss out of the smiling flowers, shining stars and dancing leaves along the way.
10) Be the creater of the reels (life experiences) not just a watcher.
11) Invest in your health! Your body is a gift , use it while you have it!

Just a few random thoughts that came into my mind then to the fingertips , while figuring out the words to write here.

Massage is my love language.
It’s not something I was taught—it came to me intuitively, since I have spent a lot of time working on my body and teaching others.
It’s amazing to witness the way our hands can communicate care, presence, and deep healing.

Each month, I take time to give myself a self-massage—a ritual of self-love and grounding. It’s my way of listening to my body and holding space for whatever it carries.

When my sister was pregnant, I would massage her often. It became our little ritual of connection. She felt nurtured, supported, and safe. Even now, she still asks for it whenever I’m home and I’m always happy to offer it.

Now, I share that same loving touch with my nephew. It’s our quiet time together, where no words are needed. Just presence, breath, and gentle care.

There’s something sacred about holding someone with your hands, with full intention and love. 

I have taught self massages wisdom in my retreats and offered massages simply to my friends and family. As of now, I don’t wish to do it professionally but would love to explore more about this.
It’s lovely to see how healing can happen through sacred physical touch. 

Your body is a gift , use it wisely✨

🤍
